title_with_entities.text: [Sign-up Sheet] Between Fandom and Femininity: Exploring Internalized Misogyny and Digital Sexism Among Young BTS Fangirls towards BLACKPINK on Facebook and X

message.text:
[LF: Philippine Respondents for a QUALITATIVE study]

Hi! We are fourth-year BA Communication students from FEU Manila, conducting our thesis entitled: “Between Fandom and Femininity: Exploring Internalized Misogyny and Digital Sexism Among Young BTS Fangirls towards BLACKPINK on Facebook and X”.

If you are:

📌A BTS Fangirl (Who might..not like BLACKPINK all that much.)

📌Aged 18 to 27 years old - Currently residing in Metro Manila

📌Have posts about BTS and BLACKPINK on Facebook/X

📌 Willing to be part of a Focus Group Discussion or One-on-one Interview (Food + Transportation to be provided)

Then you are just who we’re looking for! Come join us to talk about BTS, BLACKPINK, and the world of K-Pop fandom culture.

There’s more! Be one of the lucky participants who’ll receive FREE BTS/K-Pop Merch or ₱1,000!!

NOTE: FGDs and Interviews are scheduled to take place from September 3 - 17 2025 near FEU-Manila.

📷Scan the QR code below or click the link to register:

🔗[https://forms.gle/TxurmKjqCLwqBLGa9](https://forms.gle/TxurmKjqCLwqBLGa9?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExaDN2alhKaTFrUDNwUVlwQgEeZpBv73CJxx7b1J-YHSIj19JrEUbyVXDBTad39Mg7YQyvhxsV-fy90NR5SGk_aem_BAS50ubtvZM3fp81zWK-sA)

Should you have more questions, feel free to reach out via Messenger or through the details listed below:

Jenah Chel Javier

2022006761@feu.edu.ph

0915 092 2160
